features: The FRIGG line of moon phase rubber pacifiers is thoughtfully designed for your baby's comfort and inspired by the moon in motion. The outward curve keeps the pacifier off delicate skin, while air holes and a security handle ensure your baby stays safe.
Pack of two pacifiers. Suitable for ages 6-18 months.
100% free from BPA, PVC and phthalates.
Care Instructions: Sterilize each pacifier before use. Do not use a pacifier that shows changes in color or irregularities, though the nipple size may naturally expand with use.
body.description: A beautiful addition to your collection of baby essentials. Pacifiers available in a range of soft colors FRIGG pacifiers has been thoughtfully designed for your baby's comfort. The outward curve keeps the pacifier off their delicate skin, while features like air holes and a security handle ensure your baby stays safe. Available in a range of soft colors, FRIGG pacifiers make a beautiful addition to your collection of baby essentials. For optimal safety and hygiene, we recommend discarding your pacifier after 1-2 months of consistent use. Always check your pacifier before use, and discard at first signs of damage or wear. Natural rubber pacifiers may experience texture changes over time from exposure to extreme temperatures, humidity or direct sunlight. Replace the pacifier if the rubber material weakens.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars my son's favorite pacifier
reviews.reviewText: My son is 5 months old at this point, so I ordered the 6-18 month pair since he loved the first set of 0-6 month I got him so much. He didn't start really loving them until he was at least 3 months old. This specific pacifier is what I give him to soothe him to sleep, he will spit out the other brands. I think it's the bulb like shape. I love the design and color options too! I do think the price point is a little high for only two pacifiers though.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy for baby to hold!
reviews.reviewText: Our baby wasn’t able to hold other pacifiers in his mouth but this one worked like a charm! It’s cute, easy for him to keep in, and I love the natural rubber. It does start to show wear after about 4 weeks because he chews on it pretty hard.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Adorable, and durable
reviews.reviewText: I love these pacis, I use this and bibs interchangeably, these are adorable and honestly pretty darn durable, my one year old has beaten a lot of these up and they hold up pretty good, impressive considering they are rubber and not silicone. Don’t hesitate get these! Also side note only ones my breastfeeding baby ever took!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Only brand that works
reviews.reviewText: Only ones my little ones will use and stay in mouth!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I love these!
reviews.reviewText: My baby normally uses bibs so I’m comparing to those but I love these as well. These seem slightly bigger than the bibs. Like the features and the nipple, but it’s a very very slight difference. Will purchase again, I love the little moons it’s so stylish!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These are hands down, my son’s favorite pacifiers! They are lightweight and fit his mouth well. I appreciate that they are made of natural rubber instead of silicon because it is in his mouth all night. The color choices and designs are beautiful. The only thing not to like is the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Ended up buying more than once.
reviews.reviewText: My kid loves these pacifiers and I love that it has the phases of the moon in them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Love these but they get mold inside
reviews.reviewText: These are the ONLY pacifiers my daughter will take! We tried soo many different brands, but she will only take to these! They are definitely pricey and after a while, mold starts to form on the inside. Water gets inside them from cleaning and there’s no way to completely dry it out so seems inevitable! With that being said, you have to replace them often and that isn’t fun when they are so expensive! The glow in the dark ones only glow for about an hour.
